      "slug": "delete-duplicate-emails",
      "title": "Delete Duplicate Emails",
      "category": "Advanced String Functions / Regex / Clause",
      "difficulty": "Easy",
      "runnable": true,
      "fixtureKind": "edge",
      "hasSource": true,
      "leetcode": "https://leetcode.com/problems/delete-duplicate-emails/",
      "promptHtml": "<p>Table: <code>Person</code></p>\n<table class=\"schema\"><thead><tr>\n<th>id</th><th>int</th>\n</tr></thead><tbody>\n</tbody></table>\n<p>id is the primary key (column with unique values) for this table.</p>\n<p>Each row of this table contains an email. The emails will not contain uppercase letters.</p>\n<p>Write a solution to<strong>delete<strong> all duplicate emails, keeping only one unique email with the smallest <code>id</code>.</p>\n<p>For SQL users, please note that you are supposed to write a <code>DELETE</code> statement and not a <code>SELECT</code> one.</p>\n<p>For Pandas users, please note that you are supposed to modify <code>Person</code> in place.</p>\n<p>After running your script, the answer shown is the <code>Person</code> table. The driver will first compile and run your piece of code and then show the <code>Person</code> table. The final order of the <code>Person</code> table <strong>does not matter<strong>.</p>\n<p>The result format is in the following example.</p>\n<h3>Example 1:</h3>\n<h3>Input:</h3>\n<p>Person table:</p>\n<table class=\"schema\"><thead><tr>\n<th>1</th><th>john@example.com</th>\n</tr></thead><tbody>\n<tr><td>3</td><td>john@example.com</td></tr>\n</tbody></table>\n<h3>Output:</h3>\n<table class=\"schema\"><thead><tr>\n<th>1</th><th>john@example.com</th>\n</tr></thead><tbody>\n</tbody></table>\n<p><strong>Explanation:<strong> john@example.com is repeated two times. We keep the row with the smallest Id = 1.</p>\n<p>---</p>",
      "hint": "Keep the smallest id per email and delete rows whose id is not in that kept set.",
      "solution": "DELETE FROM Person\n            WHERE id NOT IN (\n              SELECT MIN(id)\n              FROM Person\n              GROUP BY email\n            );",
